{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":605,"text":"Growth is not dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2877,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":4263,"text":"Let's start the story 120 years ago,"},{"time":8226,"text":"when American factories began to electrify their operations,"},{"time":11858,"text":"igniting the Second Industrial Revolution."},{"time":15202,"text":"The amazing thing is"},{"time":16313,"text":"that productivity did not increase in those factories"},{"time":19090,"text":"for 30 years. Thirty years."},{"time":22346,"text":"That's long enough for a generation of managers to retire."},{"time":25820,"text":"You see, the first wave of managers"},{"time":28042,"text":"simply replaced their steam engines with electric motors,"},{"time":31459,"text":"but they didn't redesign the factories to take advantage"},{"time":34469,"text":"of electricity's flexibility."},{"time":36810,"text":"It fell to the next generation to invent new work processes,"},{"time":40794,"text":"and then productivity soared,"},{"time":43521,"text":"often doubling or even tripling in those factories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47186,"text":"Electricity is an example of a general purpose technology,"},{"time":51909,"text":"like the steam engine before it."},{"time":54139,"text":"General purpose technologies drive most economic growth,"},{"time":57555,"text":"because they unleash cascades of complementary innovations,"},{"time":61009,"text":"like lightbulbs and, yes, factory redesign."},{"time":64641,"text":"Is there a general purpose technology of our era?"},{"time":68251,"text":"Sure. It's the computer."},{"time":70759,"text":"But technology alone is not enough."},{"time":73418,"text":"Technology is not destiny."},{"time":76184,"text":"We shape our destiny,"},{"time":77764,"text":"and just as the earlier generations of managers"},{"time":80280,"text":"needed to redesign their factories,"},{"time":82578,"text":"we're going to need to reinvent our organizations"},{"time":84807,"text":"and even our whole economic system."},{"time":87362,"text":"We're not doing as well at that job as we should be."},{"time":90964,"text":"As we'll see in a moment,"},{"time":92194,"text":"productivity is actually doing all right,"},{"time":94916,"text":"but it has become decoupled from jobs,"},{"time":98778,"text":"and the income of the typical worker is stagnating."},{"time":103197,"text":"These troubles are sometimes misdiagnosed"},{"time":105716,"text":"as the end of innovation,"},{"time":109428,"text":"but they are actually the growing pains"},{"time":111557,"text":"of what Andrew McAfee and I call the new machine age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117147,"text":"Let's look at some data."},{"time":119029,"text":"So here's GDP per person in America."},{"time":121931,"text":"There's some bumps along the way, but the big story"},{"time":124697,"text":"is you could practically fit a ruler to it."},{"time":127412,"text":"This is a log scale, so what looks like steady growth"},{"time":130688,"text":"is actually an acceleration in real terms."},{"time":133731,"text":"And here's productivity."},{"time":135891,"text":"You can see a little bit of a slowdown there in the mid-'70s,"},{"time":138562,"text":"but it matches up pretty well with the Second Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":142300,"text":"when factories were learning how to electrify their operations."},{"time":144991,"text":"After a lag, productivity accelerated again."},{"time":149120,"text":"So maybe \"history doesn't repeat itself,"},{"time":151691,"text":"but sometimes it rhymes.\""},{"time":154259,"text":"Today, productivity is at an all-time high,"},{"time":157395,"text":"and despite the Great Recession,"},{"time":159372,"text":"it grew faster in the 2000s than it did in the 1990s,"},{"time":163624,"text":"the roaring 1990s, and that was faster than the '70s or '80s."},{"time":167760,"text":"It's growing faster than it did during the Second Industrial Revolution."},{"time":171434,"text":"And that's just the United States."},{"time":173177,"text":"The global news is even better."},{"time":176425,"text":"Worldwide incomes have grown at a faster rate"},{"time":178785,"text":"in the past decade than ever in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181281,"text":"If anything, all these numbers actually understate our progress,"},{"time":186332,"text":"because the new machine age"},{"time":188244,"text":"is more about knowledge creation"},{"time":189908,"text":"than just physical production."},{"time":192239,"text":"It's mind not matter, brain not brawn,"},{"time":195177,"text":"ideas not things."},{"time":197239,"text":"That creates a problem for standard metrics,"},{"time":199809,"text":"because we're getting more and more stuff for free,"},{"time":203311,"text":"like Wikipedia, Google, Skype,"},{"time":205952,"text":"and if they post it on the web, even this TED Talk."},{"time":209015,"text":"Now getting stuff for free is a good thing, right?"},{"time":212318,"text":"Sure, of course it is."},{"time":214083,"text":"But that's not how economists measure GDP."},{"time":217951,"text":"Zero price means zero weight in the GDP statistics."},{"time":223543,"text":"According to the numbers, the music industry"},{"time":225655,"text":"is half the size that it was 10 years ago,"},{"time":228655,"text":"but I'm listening to more and better music than ever."},{"time":232311,"text":"You know, I bet you are too."},{"time":234503,"text":"In total, my research estimates"},{"time":237226,"text":"that the GDP numbers miss over 300 billion dollars per year"},{"time":241980,"text":"in free goods and services on the Internet."},{"time":245326,"text":"Now let's look to the future."},{"time":247115,"text":"There are some super smart people"},{"time":249378,"text":"who are arguing that we've reached the end of growth,"},{"time":254397,"text":"but to understand the future of growth,"},{"time":257955,"text":"we need to make predictions"},{"time":260638,"text":"about the underlying drivers of growth."},{"time":263928,"text":"I'm optimistic, because the new machine age"},{"time":267734,"text":"is digital, exponential and combinatorial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272764,"text":"When goods are digital, they can be replicated"},{"time":275028,"text":"with perfect quality at nearly zero cost,"},{"time":279537,"text":"and they can be delivered almost instantaneously."},{"time":283555,"text":"Welcome to the economics of abundance."},{"time":286355,"text":"But there's a subtler benefit to the digitization of the world."},{"time":290045,"text":"Measurement is the lifeblood of science and progress."},{"time":294645,"text":"In the age of big data,"},{"time":296793,"text":"we can measure the world in ways we never could before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301079,"text":"Secondly, the new machine age is exponential."},{"time":305174,"text":"Computers get better faster than anything else ever."},{"time":311109,"text":"A child's Playstation today is more powerful"},{"time":314677,"text":"than a military supercomputer from 1996."},{"time":318733,"text":"But our brains are wired for a linear world."},{"time":321940,"text":"As a result, exponential trends take us by surprise."},{"time":325828,"text":"I used to teach my students that there are some things,"},{"time":328430,"text":"you know, computers just aren't good at,"},{"time":330364,"text":"like driving a car through traffic."},{"time":332749,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":334762,"text":"That's right, here's Andy and me grinning like madmen"},{"time":338253,"text":"because we just rode down Route 101"},{"time":340637,"text":"in, yes, a driverless car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344306,"text":"Thirdly, the new machine age is combinatorial."},{"time":346889,"text":"The stagnationist view is that ideas get used up,"},{"time":350937,"text":"like low-hanging fruit,"},{"time":352793,"text":"but the reality is that each innovation"},{"time":355956,"text":"creates building blocks for even more innovations."},{"time":359212,"text":"Here's an example. In just a matter of a few weeks,"},{"time":362557,"text":"an undergraduate student of mine"},{"time":364629,"text":"built an app that ultimately reached 1.3 million users."},{"time":368740,"text":"He was able to do that so easily"},{"time":370439,"text":"because he built it on top of Facebook,"},{"time":372266,"text":"and Facebook was built on top of the web,"},{"time":374199,"text":"and that was built on top of the Internet,"},{"time":375897,"text":"and so on and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378315,"text":"Now individually, digital, exponential and combinatorial"},{"time":383080,"text":"would each be game-changers."},{"time":385430,"text":"Put them together, and we're seeing a wave"},{"time":387620,"text":"of astonishing breakthroughs,"},{"time":389013,"text":"like robots that do factory work or run as fast as a cheetah"},{"time":392073,"text":"or leap tall buildings in a single bound."},{"time":394869,"text":"You know, robots are even revolutionizing"},{"time":397101,"text":"cat transportation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398930,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":401200,"text":"But perhaps the most important invention,"},{"time":403932,"text":"the most important invention is machine learning."},{"time":408997,"text":"Consider one project: IBM's Watson."},{"time":412373,"text":"These little dots here,"},{"time":413962,"text":"those are all the champions on the quiz show \"Jeopardy.\""},{"time":418822,"text":"At first, Watson wasn't very good,"},{"time":421366,"text":"but it improved at a rate faster than any human could,"},{"time":426988,"text":"and shortly after Dave Ferrucci showed this chart"},{"time":429675,"text":"to my class at MIT,"},{"time":431327,"text":"Watson beat the world \"Jeopardy\" champion."},{"time":434869,"text":"At age seven, Watson is still kind of in its childhood."},{"time":438858,"text":"Recently, its teachers let it surf the Internet unsupervised."},{"time":444176,"text":"The next day, it started answering questions with profanities."},{"time":450122,"text":"Damn. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452396,"text":"But you know, Watson is growing up fast."},{"time":454676,"text":"It's being tested for jobs in call centers, and it's getting them."},{"time":458888,"text":"It's applying for legal, banking and medical jobs,"},{"time":462612,"text":"and getting some of them."},{"time":464562,"text":"Isn't it ironic that at the very moment"},{"time":466451,"text":"we are building intelligent machines,"},{"time":468685,"text":"perhaps the most important invention in human history,"},{"time":472134,"text":"some people are arguing that innovation is stagnating?"},{"time":476109,"text":"Like the first two industrial revolutions,"},{"time":478528,"text":"the full implications of the new machine age"},{"time":481662,"text":"are going to take at least a century to fully play out,"},{"time":484344,"text":"but they are staggering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487376,"text":"So does that mean we have nothing to worry about?"},{"time":490712,"text":"No. Technology is not destiny."},{"time":494392,"text":"Productivity is at an all time high,"},{"time":496961,"text":"but fewer people now have jobs."},{"time":499944,"text":"We have created more wealth in the past decade than ever,"},{"time":503064,"text":"but for a majority of Americans, their income has fallen."},{"time":506968,"text":"This is the great decoupling"},{"time":509280,"text":"of productivity from employment,"},{"time":512256,"text":"of wealth from work."},{"time":515360,"text":"You know, it's not surprising that millions of people"},{"time":517706,"text":"have become disillusioned by the great decoupling,"},{"time":520552,"text":"but like too many others,"},{"time":522299,"text":"they misunderstand its basic causes."},{"time":525396,"text":"Technology is racing ahead,"},{"time":528006,"text":"but it's leaving more and more people behind."},{"time":531556,"text":"Today, we can take a routine job,"},{"time":535075,"text":"codify it in a set of machine-readable instructions,"},{"time":538166,"text":"and then replicate it a million times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540993,"text":"You know, I recently overheard a conversation"},{"time":543272,"text":"that epitomizes these new economics."},{"time":545224,"text":"This guy says, \"Nah, I don't use H&amp;R Block anymore."},{"time":549421,"text":"TurboTax does everything that my tax preparer did,"},{"time":551869,"text":"but it's faster, cheaper and more accurate.\""},{"time":556427,"text":"How can a skilled worker"},{"time":558226,"text":"compete with a $39 piece of software?"},{"time":561235,"text":"She can't."},{"time":563202,"text":"Today, millions of Americans do have faster,"},{"time":565982,"text":"cheaper, more accurate tax preparation,"},{"time":568369,"text":"and the founders of Intuit"},{"time":569855,"text":"have done very well for themselves."},{"time":572348,"text":"But 17 percent of tax preparers no longer have jobs."},{"time":576562,"text":"That is a microcosm of what's happening,"},{"time":578640,"text":"not just in software and services, but in media and music,"},{"time":583317,"text":"in finance and manufacturing, in retailing and trade --"},{"time":587003,"text":"in short, in every industry."},{"time":590898,"text":"People are racing against the machine,"},{"time":593993,"text":"and many of them are losing that race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597083,"text":"What can we do to create shared prosperity?"},{"time":600969,"text":"The answer is not to try to slow down technology."},{"time":603986,"text":"Instead of racing against the machine,"},{"time":606543,"text":"we need to learn to race with the machine."},{"time":610220,"text":"That is our grand challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613349,"text":"The new machine age"},{"time":615673,"text":"can be dated to a day 15 years ago"},{"time":618786,"text":"when Garry Kasparov, the world chess champion,"},{"time":621664,"text":"played Deep Blue, a supercomputer."},{"time":625370,"text":"The machine won that day,"},{"time":627382,"text":"and today, a chess program running on a cell phone"},{"time":630350,"text":"can beat a human grandmaster."},{"time":632646,"text":"It got so bad that, when he was asked"},{"time":636011,"text":"what strategy he would use against a computer,"},{"time":638574,"text":"Jan Donner, the Dutch grandmaster, replied,"},{"time":642590,"text":"\"I'd bring a hammer.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":644361,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648041,"text":"But today a computer is no longer the world chess champion."},{"time":652585,"text":"Neither is a human,"},{"time":655239,"text":"because Kasparov organized a freestyle tournament"},{"time":658818,"text":"where teams of humans and computers"},{"time":660734,"text":"could work together,"},{"time":662833,"text":"and the winning team had no grandmaster,"},{"time":665990,"text":"and it had no supercomputer."},{"time":668455,"text":"What they had was better teamwork,"},{"time":672630,"text":"and they showed that a team of humans and computers,"},{"time":677646,"text":"working together, could beat any computer"},{"time":680694,"text":"or any human working alone."},{"time":684214,"text":"Racing with the machine"},{"time":685878,"text":"beats racing against the machine."},{"time":688221,"text":"Technology is not destiny."},{"time":690785,"text":"We shape our destiny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692527,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693974,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}